<subSubSection id="48D355CA8F30FEBE48A753ADFE2BFA2D" pageId="382" pageNumber="383" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418F30FEBE48A753ADFB12FA49" blockId="382.[151,1438,1153,1646]" pageId="382" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F30FEBE48A753ADFE0FFB69" bold="true" box="[151,426,1153,1178]" pageId="382" pageNumber="383">Description of Female.</emphasis>
Apterous; length 
<quantity id="C731ABA48F30FEBE4AB253ADFD79FB69" box="[642,732,1153,1177]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="382" pageNumber="383" unit="mm" value="3.2">3.2 mm</quantity>
. Testaceous, except antennal segments 4–9 brown and petiole black. Antenna clavate; antennal segments in following proportions: 10:7:18:10:9:8:8:6:5.5:10; antennal segment 9 slightly longer than broad (5.5:4). Head very excavated, dull, granulated; frontal line complete; occipital carina absent; POL = 1; OL = 3; OOL = 12. Palpal formula 5/3. Pronotum shiny, weakly granulated, crossed by strong transverse impression. Scutum shiny, smooth, unsculptured. Metanotum weakly transversely striate, hollow behind scutellum, with sides protruding; lateral protrusions pointed. Metathorax + propodeum granulated; posterior surface transversely striate. Protarsal segments in following proportions: 16:4:6:19:30. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F30FEBE4D295275FA36FA81" box="[1305,1427,1369,1393]" captionStart="PLATE 118" captionStartId="380.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[270,1325,235,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-91@380.[234,1353,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="380" captionText="PLATE 118. A. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, lateral view (from Olmi 1989b). B. Furrow of metathorax + propodeum, frontal view (from Olmi 1989b). C, E. Chelae (from Olmi 1984). D. Male genitalia (from Olmi 1984). A–C. Gonatopus borneanus, holotype. D. G. borneanus, paratype. E. G. insularis, holotype. Scale bar 0.75 mm for A, 0.15 mm for C, 0.18 mm for D and 0.14 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278786" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278786/files/figure.png" pageId="382" pageNumber="383">Plate 118E</figureCitation>
) with one large subdistal tooth and one row of eight lamellae + one bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48F30FEBE4CD25251FAFEFA65" box="[1250,1371,1405,1429]" captionStart="PLATE 118" captionStartId="380.[151,233,1880,1903]" captionTargetBox="[270,1325,235,1817]" captionTargetId="figure-91@380.[234,1353,195,1858]" captionTargetPageId="380" captionText="PLATE 118. A. Scutum and metathorax + propodeum, lateral view (from Olmi 1989b). B. Furrow of metathorax + propodeum, frontal view (from Olmi 1989b). C, E. Chelae (from Olmi 1984). D. Male genitalia (from Olmi 1984). A–C. Gonatopus borneanus, holotype. D. G. borneanus, paratype. E. G. insularis, holotype. Scale bar 0.75 mm for A, 0.15 mm for C, 0.18 mm for D and 0.14 mm for E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278786" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278786/files/figure.png" pageId="382" pageNumber="383">Plate 118E</figureCitation>
) with two rows of 12 + 3 (proximal) lamellae; distal apex with about 12 lamellae. Tibial spurs 1/0/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418F30FEBE48F752E9FE2BFA2D" blockId="382.[151,1438,1153,1646]" box="[199,398,1477,1501]" pageId="382" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538F30FEBE48F752E9FEAEFA2D" bold="true" box="[199,267,1477,1501]" pageId="382" pageNumber="383">Male.</emphasis>
